1 Day Ago The attack comes few days after six soldiers were killed in an ambush along Goniri-Gorigi Road while returning from a clearance operation. Authorities of the Nigeria army have however been silent on both incidents. “They have contacted their families as usual, they will be buried in a cemetery here in Maiduguri during the week,” a source told SaharaReporters. Boko Haram and its offshoot, Islamic State West Africa Province, have killed thousands and displaced millions in North-Eastern Nigeria. Nigerian army has repeatedly claimed that the insurgency has been largely defeated and frequently underplays any losses. In the past months, soldiers have been targeted by the insurgents, waiting in ambush for them. The Boko Haram insurgency has caused over 30,000 deaths and displaced millions of individuals, mainly in Adamawa, Borno and Yobe states. The terror group wants an Islamic caliphate in northern Nigeria.